    {
      "id": "1d04a24775cd5ab04ca462d82c022512e69551c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 378,
        "name": "Sergey Cheremencev",
        "email": "scherementsev@ddn.com",
        "username": "scheremencev"
      },
      "date": "2024-06-03 12:25:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Hongchao, can you please answer Sergey's question.\n> \n> Sergey, is that a reason to block landing?  Does it slow down testing performance during normal operation?\n\nI'm not aware about any testing problems. Commit message says what fix is doing, but it's not clear why do we need to do that. At first look after setting force_reint we just need to wait until some limit on qsd will be changed. What if it is not changed after a 1st try because of some problem in qsd code and we need to sort it out instead of fixing the test case? Or probably qsd could be not ready for some reasons and it is a valid case to set force_reint multiple times. So just wanted to know that before setting +1.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "765a08b87d7c869e08add7a032f70b4a1759dc07",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 144,
        "name": "Hongchao Zhang",
        "email": "hongchao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "Hongchao.zhang"
      },
      "date": "2024-06-04 02:33:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> > Patch Set 3:\n> > \n> > Hongchao, can you please answer Sergey's question.\n> > \n> > Sergey, is that a reason to block landing?  Does it slow down testing performance during normal operation?\n> \n> I'm not aware about any testing problems. Commit message says what fix is doing, but it's not clear why do we need to do that. At first look after setting force_reint we just need to wait until some limit on qsd will be changed. What if it is not changed after a 1st try because of some problem in qsd code and we need to sort it out instead of fixing the test case? Or probably qsd could be not ready for some reasons and it is a valid case to set force_reint multiple times. So just wanted to know that before setting +1.\n\nHi\nThanks\nBy trying to reint multiply time just to make sure the Quota re-integration are actually\ninitiated on the QSD and gotten the update quote setting information from QMT\n(it maybe could fail for some network issue?).\nUnfortunately, There seemed no special logs found in QMT/QSD to indicate why the quota\nsettings were not synched into QSD from QMT in the previous test failures.\nWill try to look at more test failed logs to check whether some new clues to be found.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
